info.headline: Flood Warning issued June 3 at 3:17PM CDT until June 4 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Wichita KS
info.description:
...The National Weather Service in Wichita KS has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Kansas...
West Branch Walnut River at El Dorado affecting Butler County.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and major flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...West Branch Walnut River at El Dorado.
* WHEN...From this afternoon to tomorrow evening.
* IMPACTS...At 25.0 feet, Roads flood in northeast El Dorado between 8th Avenue and 12th Avenue. Then 10 miles north of El Dorado, flood waters cover county roads from northwest 75th to 110th.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 3:00 PM CDT Tuesday the stage was 21.5 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 26.0 feet just after midnight tonight. It will then fall below flood stage tomorrow morning. - Flood stage is 21.0 feet.
info.instruction:
Do not drive into flooded areas or go around barricades. Nearly two feet of water will carry most vehicles away. Turn around, don't drown.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.
The next statement will be issued late tonight at 330 AM CDT.

parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS AFTERNOON TO TOMORROW EVENING
